Program: In Our Time
Title: Episode 1
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b018wfsc
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 2 Jan 2012
Melvyn Bragg investigates the development of the written word and how it has shaped our intellectual history. In this first programme he looks at the technology of writing, arguably our most important invention. He examines some of the oldest surviving writing implements, and discovers and how making signs on clay, wood or parchment enabled the development of human culture. Producer: Thomas Morris. Show less